          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " Pu-242 sample :",
                " Production method           Molecular plating",
                " Chemical composition        Pu(OH)4",
                " Diameter (mm)               29.95 +- 0.03",
                " Activity (MBq)              0.0915 +- 0.0003",
                " Mass (microg)               625 +- 5",
                " Areal density (microg/cm2)  88.7 +- 0.8",
                " Isotopic purity             99.96518(45)%",
                "  The mass and areal density were deduced using the",
                " 242Pu alpha half-life 3.73E+5 yr.",
                " The isotopic composition was measured by mass",
                " spectroscopy.",
                " 239Pu, 241Pu, and 244Pu contribute < 0.06% to the",
                " activity.",
                " Distance neutron source - IOCH front wall was 44-50 mm",
                " with a 0.5 mm uncertainty.",
                " The activity of the Pu deposit was measured to be",
                " 0.0915 +- 0.0003 MBq on April 7, 2011.",
                " The mass of the deposit 0.625 +- 0.005 mg was",
                " calculated from the activity measurement.",
                " The isotopic composition was determined by mass",
                " spectroscopy on May 12, 2011.",
                " There was insignificant loss of 242Pu, 0.0003%, due to",
                " alpha decay in the time from activity measurement to",
                " the experiment date."
              ]
            }
